<reference id="api_imediaplayer_setloopcount">
    <title><ph keyref="setLoopCount"/></title>
    <shortdesc id="short"><ph id="shortdesc" props="cpp">Sets the number of times the audio effect loops.</ph><ph id="shortdesc" props="android">Sets the number of times the audio effect is looped.</ph></shortdesc>
    <prolog>
        <metadata>
            <keywords>
                <indexterm keyref="setLoopCount"/>
            </keywords>
        </metadata>
    </prolog>
    <refbody>
        <section id="prototype">
            <p outputclass="codeblock">
                <codeblock props="cpp" outputclass="language-cpp">virtual int setLoopCount(int loopCount) = 0;</codeblock>
                <codeblock props="android" outputclass="language-java">int setLoopCount(int loopCount);</codeblock>
            </p>
        </section>
        <section id="detailed_desc" deliveryTarget="details" otherprops="no-title">
            <p props="cpp">Call this method to set the number of times the audio effect loops. After all loops complete, the SDK triggers the <xref keyref="onPlayerSourceStateChanged"/> callback and reports the playback state as <codeph>PLAYER_STATE_PLAYBACK_ALL_LOOPS_COMPLETED</codeph>.</p>
            <note props="android">After looping playback completes, the SDK triggers the <xref keyref="onPlayerSourceStateChanged"/> callback and reports the playback state as <codeph>PLAYER_STATE_PLAYBACK_ALL_LOOPS_COMPLETED</codeph>.</note>
        </section>
        <section id="parameters" deliveryTarget="details" props="android cpp">
            <title>Parameters</title>
            <parml>
                <plentry props="cpp">
                    <pt>loopCount</pt>
                    <pd>The number of times the audio effect loops:
                        <ul>
                            <li>≥ 0: The number of times to play. For example, 0 means no loop, play once only; 1 means loop once, play twice in total.</li>
                            <li>-1: Loop the audio file infinitely.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </pd>
                </plentry>
                <plentry props="android">
                    <pt>loopCount</pt>
                    <pd>The number of times the audio effect is looped:
                        <ul>
                            <li>≥ 0: Number of times to play. For example, 0 means no looping, play once only; 1 means loop once, play twice in total.</li>
                            <li>-1: Loop the audio file infinitely.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </pd>
                </plentry>
            </parml>
        </section>
        <section id="return_values" props="android cpp">
            <title>Return Values</title>
            <p props="cpp">
                <ul>
                    <li>0: Success.</li>
                    <li>&lt; 0: Failure.</li>
                </ul>
            </p>
            <p props="android">
                <ul>
                    <li>0: The method call succeeds.</li>
                    <li>&lt; 0: The method call fails.</li>
                </ul>
            </p>
        </section>
    </refbody>
</reference>